commentTextItems.html: there he goes again, Gayle has smashed it straight this time and it's another six

commentPostTextItems.html: Oh dear, that didn't last long. the players have left the field again as the rain returns.
So, 17 runs from those 11 balls will have done West Indies no harm at all, they will be worried by this weather though. Updates as they come

commentTextItems.html: smashed off the back foot over extra-cover and away for another Gayle boundary
driven on the off side
full toss on leg stump and just clipped to deep square for a single

headshotImage.caption: Mark Gillespie player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mark Gillespie player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: short again and Gayle just moves his head out the way
short again and he pulls it through midwicket. Didn't quite get hold of it and is picked up on the rope
that comes back into him and it falls harmlessly on the off side
short again and he gets out the way this time
short and Chattergoon has picked that up well off his hips and it beats Flynn on the boundary
pushed to mid-off

commentPreTextItems.html: 5.40pm OK, word is play will start at 5.50pm, so that's ten minutes away, and we will have a 40 Over match. I'll let you know the target when I hear.
West Indies will need to score another 188 in 31.2 overs, so that's a total of 235 in 40 overs.
5.30pm Still not much to report I'm afraid. I, like everyone else, am still waiting to hear something. You'll know as soon as I do.

5.05pm It's still raining quite heavily I'm afraid, and the covers won't be coming off any time soon. Fingers crossed this blows over because this match is looking very good right now - there will almost certainly be a reduction of overs however.
4.45pm Well, it looks like more than just a shower right now, it's coming down pretty hard. I'll keep you updated as things develop.

commentTextItems.html: guided down to third man

commentPostTextItems.html: The fielding side have also taken a power play

commentTextItems.html: defended back to the bowler once again

commentPostTextItems.html: And off they go. The Umpires have decided the rain is heavy enough to take the players off, lets hope this is just a shower.

commentTextItems.html: full and defended
driven through mid-off again and really well fielded by Vettori, diving to pull it back from the rope and saving one.

commentPostTextItems.html: The rain is starting to move in and people are heading for cover

commentTextItems.html: squares him up again a little, but safely defended
not that short but it gets up and Chattergoon defends off his chest. He's not a particularly big chap mind you.

commentPostTextItems.html: Very good start by Gayle and Chattergoon here, just what West Indies needed

headshotImage.caption: Mark Gillespie player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mark Gillespie player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: wide again and driven behind point and they push for two
full and finally he times one. Flicked over mid-on and away for his first boundary
pushed on the off side again but easily fielded
driven through the off but not timed at all so is chased down by Vettori

commentPreTextItems.html: 6.55pm - Match Abandoned Well, there it is, the news none of us wanted. A real shame as this game was looking really good. What it does mean however is that on Tuesday we will have a winner takes all clash in Napier.

Thanks for joining me, Alan Curr, for what was so nearly a great game. Still, we have a little piece of history after the knock by Martin Guptill and New Zealand will certainly be happy with the contribution of him, Ross Taylor and Neil Broom, while Lionel Baker and Chris Gayle were the pick for West Indies.
6.35pm Covers are still on I'm afraid and not much happening out there. It's dark, wet and a little miserable.
6.15pm This really is rather irritating, the game is set up so nicely, Gayle is batting like a King, and we're all sat watching the rain. It doesn't look great out there either.
